FBIS4-58634 "drnes088_o_94001" FBIS-NES-94-088 Daily Report 6 May 1994 SYRIA Al-Asad Urges Yemen's Leaders To Preserve Unity Al-Asad Urges Yemen's Leaders To Preserve Unity JN0605081794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0415 GMT 6 May 94 JN0605081794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad has held two telephone conversations with Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and his deputy 'Ali Salim al-Bid. Talks during the two conversations dealt with the situation in Yemen and the ongoing battles on Yemeni territory. President Hafiz al-Asad stressed Syria's pressing desire that all parties should work to halt the ongoing battles and resort to dialogue stemming from concern about the safety of Yemeni citizens in a way that will preserve Yemen's national unity.
